# Implementation Plan: Cloud Migration & Optimization

This plan analyzes whether moving from Render to AWS or Azure Free Services is beneficial for the **AI Job Matching Project** and provides a roadmap for the transition.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Credit Card Requirement**: Both AWS and Azure require a valid credit card for account verification, even for free tiers. Render has a more "card-less" entry point for some services.
> 
> **Maintenance Overhead**: Moving to AWS/Azure increases infrastructure complexity. Unlike Render (which is PaaS), you will likely manage an EC2 instance (IaaS), meaning you are responsible for OS updates and security patches.

## Comparison Analysis

| Feature | Render (Current) | AWS (Recommended) | Azure |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Database (PostgreSQL)** | Free tier expires in 30 days. | **RDS PostgreSQL (750h/mo for 12mo)**. Persistent for a year. | Limited free tier, often harder to configure for `pgvector`. |
| **`pgvector` Support** | Yes | **Yes (Highly stable on RDS)** | Yes |
| **Backend (FastAPI)** | Spins down after 15m (Cold starts). | **EC2 t2.micro (750h/mo for 12mo)**. Always awake. | App Service F1 tier (Always up, but very low RAM). |
| **Background Tasks** | Hard to run on free tier (scales to paid). | **Perfect for EC2**. Run Celery/Redis in the background easily. | Logic Apps or Functions (Adds complexity). |
| **Setup Complexity** | Very Low | **High** (IAM, VPC, Security Groups) | Medium/High |

