## Proposed Changes

We will move the high-value components (Database and Backend) to AWS while keeping the Frontend on Vercel for the best performance and simplified SSL.

### [Phase 1] Database Migration (AWS RDS)

Migrate the database to AWS RDS to gain a 12-month persistent storage window.

#### [NEW] AWS RDS Instance
- Provision a `db.t3.micro` (or `db.t4g.micro` if available in region) running PostgreSQL 16+.
- Enable `pgvector` extension.
- Update `.env` with the new `DATABASE_URL`.

### [Phase 2] Backend Deployment (AWS EC2)

Deploy the FastAPI backend and Job Scrapers to an EC2 instance to ensure they stay active 24/7.

#### [MODIFY] [Dockerfile](file:///t:/DO_IT_NOW_OR_NEVER/AI_PROJECTS/AI%20Job%20Matching%20Project/backend/Dockerfile)
- Optimize Dockerfile for production (multi-stage builds).
- Ensure it handles secrets via environment variables instead of hardcoding.

#### [NEW] [docker-compose.prod.yml](file:///t:/DO_IT_NOW_OR_NEVER/AI_PROJECTS/AI%20Job%20Matching%20Project/backend/docker-compose.prod.yml)
- Define services for `api`, `worker` (Celery), and `redis`.
- Set up automatic restarts.

### [Phase 3] Frontend Connection

Update the Vercel deployment to point to the new AWS EC2 endpoint.

#### [MODIFY] [vercel.json](file:///t:/DO_IT_NOW_OR_NEVER/AI_PROJECTS/AI%20Job%20Matching%20Project/frontend/vercel.json)
- Update environment variables to point to the AWS Elastic IP or domain name.

